<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="361" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,799,824]" pageId="10" pageNumber="361">Remarks</emphasis>
. The species described above is in most respects similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert" authorityName="Grootaert" box="[973,1204,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dessarti">
<emphasis box="[973,1090,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="361">P. dessarti</emphasis>
Grootaert
</taxonomicName>
known from Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Grootaert" box="[158,449,836,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="361" refString="Grootaert, P. &amp; Chvala, M. (1992) Monograph of the genus Platypalpus (Diptera: Empidoidea, Hybotidae) of the Mediterranean region and the Canary Islands. Acta Universitatis Carolinae-Biologica, 36, 3 - 226." type="journal article" year="1992">
Grootaert &amp; Chvála 
<number box="[389,449,836,860]" pageId="10" pageNumber="361" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); however, the latter species has a yellow abdomen.
</paragraph>
